 Task 5: Risk Category Tagging 
Create a new list called risk_category: 
• Age < 30 → "Low Risk"  
• Age 30–45 → "Medium Risk"  
• Age > 45 → "High Risk" 
----------------------------------------

Code:
category = []
for age in customer_age:
  if age < 30:
    category.append("Low Risk")
  elif age >= 30 and age <= 45:
    category.append("Medium Risk")
  else:
    category.append("High Risk")
risk_category = list(zip(customer_age, category))
for status in risk_category:
  print(status)

Output:
(25, 'Low Risk')
(45, 'Medium Risk')
(35, 'Medium Risk')
(50, 'High Risk')
(23, 'Low Risk')
(40, 'Medium Risk')



